Change has been successfully merged
As-written, looks correct to me.  Just needs combined with the next patch.
Note that this patch is intended to merged at the same time as the next patch in the chain.
I think this could go on its own. Doesn't do anything but static data.
It should be safe to be merged by itself since it passed the service validator.  See https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/61064/comments/885a9ae6_0c79f988
I reran the service validator using just this patch and it passed.  Based on that I agree it should be fine to merge on its own
Note that this should be AggregationSourceCollection and it should be moved up to before the "- Members" line.  It's been corrected in th next patch in the chain.
I just went ahead and fixed this in the current patch.
